# ====================================================================
# Roo Code Workspace Protection Ignore File
# Tailored for Phase 3-6: Templates, Ingestion, GEO SEO, and Sitemaps
# ====================================================================

# 1. Block massive text/JSON dependency graphs (The biggest token consumers)
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml
bun.lockb

# 2. Block compiled/build outputs and environments
node_modules/
dist/
build/
out/
coverage/
.env*
!.env.example

# 3. Block media and large static assets (Prevents image/PDF parsing token leaks)
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.webp
*.gif
*.svg
*.ico
*.pdf
public/images/
public/docs/

# 4. Block OS metadata and caches
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.log
.git/
.github/
.vscode/
.cursor/

# ====================================================================
# Whitelist / Context Rules (Explicitly allowed paths for your tasks)
# ====================================================================
# Allowed by default if not caught above:
# - src/templates/ (Phase 3)
# - src/content/ (Phase 4 & 5)
# - src/components/SEO.tsx (Phase 5)
# - public/robots.txt & root level scripts (Phase 6)